   <h1>Corn buses mini trip report</h1>
   <b>"Accessys(-at-)smart.net" <accessys(-at-)smart.net></b><br/>
   <i>2009-08-10 23:21:38+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>WOW!!!!  those Canadians sure know how to throw a party.....

added a couple extra days to my visit to the wilderness up north so
left Baltimore 8:15AM and drove up thru PA & NY via Rt 15 & 20
spending Tue Night at the Lake Darian state Park just East of Buffalo.

up bright and early Wed and start North,  the poor lady at Canadian
imigration made the mistake of asking me where I was headed, just a
Bus get together, I fortunately had printed out the flyer for Buses of
the Corn and handed it to her.   the look on her face said', "now I've
seen it all" but wished me a good time and I entered Canada and the
long construction project called the QEW highway.  picked up the key
for Greg and easily found the Heber Downs site.
  found a spot and about 7:30 decided to get an early start the next
day.   next thing I know about a half dozen bus pilots arrive to
welcome me and get an early start. soon there was a campfire and all
was good. finally got to bed almost midnight.

Thur took the train into Toronto and played the tourist thing.
got back to Heber Downs about 6 and set up camp for the stay. Frank
was already there and soon we had another half dozen buses and more
firewood.  while we were unloading and setting up camps, Gregs
youngest daughter decided to start the campfire for us,  and a great
fire starter she was indeed. again there was more getting caught up on
busing.  again a late night settling in, but was fun.

Fri things really got going, one bus after the other pulling in every
few minutes. (mostly vanagons, it seems) good food, good fun, and lots
of checking out each others rides.

Sat was the ever fantastic FMBC breakfast burritos. almost nothing
more can be said other than I skipped Lunch no room. the tiedyeing
event produced much fine art. some interesting bus stuff to take home.
  and then the main event!! some of the sweetest best tasting corn I
have ever had, certainly the best North of the Mason/Dixon line....
and more talk and more talk and the awards,  and I won another VW bus,
ok radio controled and about a half meter long. but super cool. seems
I had come the furtherest, just barely beating out Mike Benthin from
New Jersey.</pre>


